  "response": "The device you are referring to on an umpire's arm is likely a pitch counter or a timing device. In baseball, a pitch counter helps umpires keep track of the number of pitches thrown by the pitcher, while a timing device can be used to ensure that the game progresses at a proper pace. With the introduction of pitch clocks in some leagues, umpires may also use these devices to monitor and enforce time limits between pitches.",
